# Parallel agent collision safety

When unexpected edits or files appear, assume parallel work may be happening.

- Read `.cursor/agent-intents/BOARD.md` before editing shared areas.
- Before editing, deleting, staging, or committing, check whether another agent
  may be working in the same area.
- Strong signals include unexpected modified or untracked files, active entries
  on the intent board, new orchestrator outputs, or user context that suggests
  multiple agents are active.
- If overlap is plausible, do not guess file ownership.
- Prefer a safe strategy:
  - narrow work to non-overlapping files
  - re-read the affected files and current git status before editing
  - stage only files you changed yourself
  - ask the user before touching ambiguous changes
- Never overwrite, delete, or commit another agent's changes without explicit
  confirmation.
- If parallel work is intentional, register your intent on the board and think
  through a collision-avoidance plan before continuing mechanically.

## Before `git push` (shared `master`)

Remediation pushas till **`origin/master`**. **Direkt före `git push`:** kör `git fetch origin` och `git pull origin master` (vid behov `git pull --rebase origin master`) så commits från andra agenter integreras först. Se även `docs/plans/active/external-review-execution/CONTINUATION.md` § *Principer*.
